    "This property is vital for selecting materials such as cement, as it directly affects surface area and is fundamental to key material characteristics.",
    "Fineness significantly impacts workability, setting time, strength, and hydration rate, establishing it as a critical determinant of concrete performance.",
    "For materials with high reactivity, an increase in fineness often necessitates additional water, which can increase the risk of shrinkage.",
    "As indicated in the table below, materials such as SF and MK possess the highest fineness values.",
    "This elevated fineness contributes to superior mechanical properties due to the fine particles enhanced pore-filling capacity and rapid pozzolanic activity, resulting in a denser matrix with reduced permeability."
